"Shy doesn't think
he's God's gift to the world,

39:20.484 --> 39:22.736
- but he does call his suits his wrapping paper."
- I get it.

39:22.736 --> 39:25.655
You are a treasure trove
of punch lines.

39:25.739 --> 39:28.200
But I never would have hurt you.

39:29.284 --> 39:31.912
Not on purpose.
Not for anything in the world.

39:31.912 --> 39:33.872
I thought we were friends.

39:33.872 --> 39:36.833
And I take my friendships
very seriously.

39:36.917 --> 39:40.462
I know how loaded
what I said was,

39:40.462 --> 39:42.255
and if I could take it back,
I would.

39:42.339 --> 39:44.508
If you had just let me
on that plane,

39:44.508 --> 39:46.551
I would have said I was sorry.

39:46.635 --> 39:49.179
And not to keep my job.
I'll get another job.

39:49.179 --> 39:54.017
But because I was
and still am truly sorry.

39:56.103 --> 39:57.854
If I'd have let you
on that plane,

39:57.938 --> 39:59.314
you would've brought Susie,

39:59.314 --> 40:01.775
and she would've tried
to stab me with a cheese knife.

40:01.775 --> 40:03.777
And I would have thrown myself
in front of you

40:03.777 --> 40:05.362
and taken the blow.

40:05.362 --> 40:06.863
And some Brie.

40:08.281 --> 40:09.866
Well...

40:11.868 --> 40:13.870
I sure have missed that brisket.

40:16.289 --> 40:18.458
I'll send Monica the recipe.

40:22.295 --> 40:25.423
You know, I'm back in the States

40:25.507 --> 40:27.175
for a while again next month.

40:27.259 --> 40:28.802
Cut another Christmas album.

40:28.802 --> 40:31.721
Hmm. I know what to get
my mother for Hanukkah.

40:31.805 --> 40:34.349
Maybe we could,
uh, get together,

40:34.349 --> 40:37.144
have a drink.
I-I could take you to...

40:37.144 --> 40:38.687
- No.
- No?

40:38.687 --> 40:40.647
I'm not falling for that again.

40:40.647 --> 40:42.607
We're not friends.

40:42.691 --> 40:44.693
I have learned my lesson.

40:48.697 --> 40:50.907
Congratulations.

40:50.991 --> 40:54.744
I hope you're gonna be
very happy...

40:54.828 --> 40:56.830
Dwayne.

41:05.255 --> 41:06.756
That's what I'm saying.

41:06.840 --> 41:09.134
- Can we get out of here?
- Yeah, sure.

41:09.134 --> 41:11.136
Bye. Thanks for the croutons.

41:11.136 --> 41:13.638
- I ate everybody's croutons.
- Who let them in?

41:13.722 --> 41:16.224
Ladies,
would you come with us, please?

41:16.308 --> 41:17.559
We have invites.

41:17.559 --> 41:19.644
They checked them
at the door and everything.

41:27.694 --> 41:28.945
He still there?

41:29.029 --> 41:30.071
- Yep.
- He still big?

41:30.155 --> 41:31.072
- Yep.
- Mm.

41:40.207 --> 41:42.542
- Lou.
- Susie Myerson.

41:42.626 --> 41:45.462
And Mrs. Maisel.
It's nice to see you.

41:45.462 --> 41:47.672
- What is this, Lou?
- I want you to meet my associate,

41:47.756 --> 41:49.090
Ken Bruni.

41:49.174 --> 41:51.509
Ken is Shy's new agent
over at MCA.

41:51.593 --> 41:53.970
Very nice to meet you, ladies.
Enjoying the party?

41:54.054 --> 41:56.556
- Up until our abduction, it was great.
- Well,

41:56.640 --> 41:57.766
we just wanted to say hello

41:57.766 --> 42:00.477
and fill you in
on some exciting news.

42:00.477 --> 42:03.230
Shy's going to be the lead
in Billy Wilder's next film.

42:03.230 --> 42:04.648
Did you know he could act?

42:04.648 --> 42:06.316
I thought today's performance
was pretty good.

42:06.316 --> 42:07.859
I'll cut to the chase.

42:07.943 --> 42:09.486
Everyone here

42:09.486 --> 42:12.155
is aware of Shy's proclivities.

42:12.239 --> 42:15.784
But from now on,
we're gonna help him

42:15.784 --> 42:17.077
to stay
on the straight and narrow.

42:17.077 --> 42:19.329
Watch over him 24 hours a day.

42:19.329 --> 42:21.706
- Isn't that what Reggie does?
- Reggie's gone.

42:21.790 --> 42:22.916
Gone?

42:22.916 --> 42:24.501
- Holy shit.
- Look,

42:24.501 --> 42:26.962
he's a good guy, Reggie.
I like him.

42:26.962 --> 42:28.922
But he's too close with Shy

42:28.922 --> 42:31.132
to control him.
There's too much history.

42:31.216 --> 42:33.843
- And too much history with the band, too, huh?
- Exactly.

42:33.927 --> 42:35.387
Shy fought it,
but eventually he realized

42:35.387 --> 42:37.013
it was time
to chart a new course.

42:37.097 --> 42:39.557
All this because I cracked
a couple Judy Garland jokes

42:39.641 --> 42:41.142
- at the Apollo?
- No,

42:41.226 --> 42:43.061
no, this has been
a long time coming.

42:43.061 --> 42:45.397
That night at the Apollo
just gave us an opening.

42:45.397 --> 42:46.690
So, thank you.

42:46.690 --> 42:48.692
Reggie got Shy
to where he is now.

42:48.692 --> 42:51.194
- You realize that?
- Reggie's taken care of.

42:51.278 --> 42:53.488
Big severance.
We threw him some publishing.

42:53.488 --> 42:55.282
He's buying a house
in Westchester.

42:55.282 --> 42:57.325
- Everybody's happy.
- Oh, I bet.

42:57.409 --> 42:58.994
'Cause when you think Reggie,
you think Westchester.

42:58.994 --> 43:01.079
All right, Lou. Suit guy.

43:01.079 --> 43:03.164
- Ken.
- Thanks for filling us in

43:03.248 --> 43:04.624
on a bunch of stuff
we didn't give a fuck about.

43:04.708 --> 43:05.792
Okay for us to go?

43:05.792 --> 43:07.502
Just another minute
of your time.

43:07.502 --> 43:10.297
We understand you and Shy
got pretty friendly on tour

43:10.297 --> 43:12.215
and that maybe you saw
some things.

43:12.299 --> 43:15.010
One thing in particular
that occurred on a boat.

43:15.010 --> 43:17.637
We know that you thought
you were helping him,

43:17.721 --> 43:19.472
so the way it ended up with you
on the tarmac that night,

43:19.556 --> 43:22.309
it doesn't seem right.
We want to make it right.

43:22.309 --> 43:23.852
Okay.

43:23.852 --> 43:25.812
How does $2,000 sound?

43:25.812 --> 43:27.689
Two thousand dollars? Wow.

43:27.689 --> 43:30.442
- You want to give me $2,000?
- In exchange

43:30.442 --> 43:32.152
for your signature
on a legal agreement

43:32.152 --> 43:34.696
stating that you won't disparage
or besmirch Shy Baldwin

43:34.696 --> 43:37.032
in any way,
publicly or privately.

43:37.032 --> 43:39.075
You invited me
so you could bribe me?

43:39.159 --> 43:40.660
It's not a bribe.
It's an agreement.

43:40.744 --> 43:42.954
There is no way I would
ever take $2,000 from you.

43:43.038 --> 43:45.874
Uh, yeah, right.
Fuck you and your $2,000.

43:45.874 --> 43:48.335
- How about three?
- Miriam?

43:48.335 --> 43:51.212
- Nope. Three? Forget it.
- Five.

43:51.296 --> 43:53.423
Now, this is getting
very interesting.

43:53.423 --> 43:55.717
- Keep it.
- Yep.

43:55.717 --> 43:58.636
We thought about it.
Not fucking interested.

43:58.720 --> 44:00.805
- Ten.
- Okay, Miriam, that's a car.

44:00.889 --> 44:03.475
Three cars
or one big, fancy German car.

44:03.475 --> 44:05.685
- A shiny, nazi Mercedes.
- No.

44:05.769 --> 44:07.729
- No.
- Fuck! No.

44:07.729 --> 44:09.314
Last and best. Twelve.

44:09.314 --> 44:11.274
Oh, are there harps
playing somewhere?

44:11.358 --> 44:12.984
- I'm hearing harps.
- We're done here.

44:13.068 --> 44:14.194
- We are?
- Yes.

44:14.194 --> 44:15.278
- Come on.
- We'd like you

44:15.362 --> 44:16.571
to reconsider. The offer's gone

44:16.571 --> 44:17.739
as soon as
you walk out the door.

44:17.739 --> 44:19.240
I promised Shy
I would never tell anyone

44:19.324 --> 44:20.450
about that night, and I haven't.

44:20.450 --> 44:22.327
I promised Shy.

44:22.327 --> 44:24.245
Let's go.

44:24.329 --> 44:25.997
- Unless you want to...
- I want nothing from them.

44:26.081 --> 44:28.917
Yep, me, neither.
Let's go. Fuck you.

44:28.917 --> 44:30.502
Stupid idea to come here.

44:30.502 --> 44:32.837
- Was that aimed at me?
- No. Yes.

44:32.921 --> 44:35.590
- This was your idea.
- My idea? If it wasn't for you,

44:35.590 --> 44:36.883
I wouldn't have found
my invite to this thing

44:36.883 --> 44:38.968
for, like, ten months,
so this is your fault.

44:39.052 --> 44:40.553
Fuck it.
We're getting gift bags.

44:40.637 --> 44:43.181
That's tacky. I bet there's not
even anything good...

44:43.181 --> 44:44.891
Oh, my God, it's Chanel No. 5.

44:44.891 --> 44:47.102
- Get one for Grandma Mary.
- Who?

44:47.102 --> 44:49.354
Our grandmother
who couldn't come tonight

44:49.354 --> 44:51.689
but was also invited
and loves Chanel No. 5.

44:51.773 --> 44:54.192
- Got it.
- I'll meet you outside.

45:13.086 --> 45:15.338
- Where the hell were you?
- I was looking for a cab.

45:15.422 --> 45:17.173
You told me,
"Meet me out front."

45:17.257 --> 45:18.716
There weren't any cabs
out front, so I thought

45:18.800 --> 45:20.009
I'd go around the corner
because I remembered

45:20.093 --> 45:21.261
that whenever I shop
at Bergdorf's,

45:21.261 --> 45:22.846
I always go out the side door
to grab a cab

45:22.846 --> 45:25.098
- before they turn onto Fifth.
- I got this cab on Fifth.

45:25.098 --> 45:26.808
Well, it's not a foolproof plan.

45:26.808 --> 45:28.309
Just get in the goddamn car.

45:28.393 --> 45:29.978
Next time, I leave you here.

45:52.834 --> 45:55.253
<i>♪ Baby...</i>

45:55.253 --> 45:57.589
- The till's over.
- Over?

45:57.589 --> 45:59.507
That's not possible.
I did the count myself.

45:59.591 --> 46:01.092
I counted twice.
There's an extra five.

46:01.176 --> 46:02.886
Give it. I must've screwed up.

46:02.886 --> 46:04.512
Thanks for catching it.

46:04.596 --> 46:07.724
- You know this guy?
- Pop. What are you doing here?

46:07.724 --> 46:09.058
I was in the area

46:09.142 --> 46:11.019
seeing one of my notions
and trimmings guys

46:11.019 --> 46:12.187
and thought I'd stop by.

46:12.187 --> 46:13.688
Well, come on in.
I'll spot you a drink.

46:13.688 --> 46:15.190
Place looks good.

46:15.190 --> 46:18.902
The decor, the ambience.
Very impressive.

46:18.902 --> 46:21.154
Last time I was here,
it was covered in buttons.

46:21.154 --> 46:23.698
- Couple of whiskies for me and my pop.
- You got it, boss.

46:23.698 --> 46:25.575
"Boss."
I like the sound of that.

46:25.575 --> 46:28.119
- It does not get old.
- You know that the key

46:28.203 --> 46:31.080
to a great relationship
with your employees is respect.

46:31.164 --> 46:32.916
In order for them
to be productive,

46:32.916 --> 46:34.626
they got to think
you trust them unconditionally.

46:34.626 --> 46:36.503
- Absolutely.
- But every one of them's a thief,

46:36.503 --> 46:38.254
- so don't trust a single one.
- I know.

46:38.338 --> 46:40.715
I put an extra five in the till,
and he called it out.

46:40.715 --> 46:43.176
And didn't pocket it.
That means he's a keeper.

46:43.176 --> 46:45.386
I was taught by the best.

46:45.470 --> 46:46.888
Thanks.

46:46.888 --> 46:48.640
Any chance
your girlfriend's around?

46:48.640 --> 46:51.309
No. It's crunch time
at school for her.

46:51.309 --> 46:53.770
- Always with the books.
- In the summer?

46:53.770 --> 46:55.939
- It's medical school.
- Medical school.

46:55.939 --> 46:57.148
Well, well, well.

46:57.232 --> 46:59.234
She sounds interesting,
this girl.

46:59.234 --> 47:01.069
She is. She's great.

47:01.069 --> 47:03.988
With a lot of different sides
to her. Conflicting sides.

47:04.072 --> 47:06.241
- What?
- Well, the other night,

47:06.241 --> 47:07.659
the first half of dinner,
she was Rachel,

47:07.659 --> 47:09.369
sometime before kugel,
she was Rebecca,

47:09.369 --> 47:11.329
after kugel she was Ruth.
You kept them biblical.

47:11.329 --> 47:13.164
- That was nice.
- I was nervous.

47:13.248 --> 47:15.792
- And I corrected myself. You remember that, right?
- I do.

47:15.792 --> 47:17.335
Just trying to think
when was the last time

47:17.335 --> 47:19.128
I called Shirley
Sheila or Trudy.

47:19.212 --> 47:21.130
Or had to think
for a couple of seconds

47:21.214 --> 47:22.715
when somebody asked how we met.

47:22.799 --> 47:24.842
Ma's questions come
pretty fast and furious, Pop.

47:24.926 --> 47:26.636
- You know that.
- Mm-hmm.

47:26.636 --> 47:28.596
Listen, so you know,

47:28.680 --> 47:30.890
what I know
is all I need to know.

47:30.974 --> 47:33.601
- I don't know.
- You like her.

47:33.685 --> 47:35.728
That's all I know.
That's all I need to know.

47:35.812 --> 47:39.399
But keep in mind
your mother is very excited

47:39.399 --> 47:40.817
about Rachel Rebecca Ruth,

47:40.817 --> 47:42.694
and when she gets excited
about something

47:42.694 --> 47:44.195
and that something
disappoints her,

47:44.279 --> 47:46.239
our house
gets very small and loud.

47:46.239 --> 47:48.074
- I get it.
- The good news is

47:48.074 --> 47:50.326
your dinner appearance
got you a little reprieve

47:50.410 --> 47:51.536
from her trying to set you up

47:51.536 --> 47:53.538
with every single Jewish girl
she sees,

47:53.538 --> 47:55.248
including your cousin Rachel.

47:55.248 --> 47:57.125
You can start answering
your phone again.

47:57.125 --> 47:58.459
Great.

47:58.543 --> 48:00.753
So, there really is a girl?

48:00.837 --> 48:02.880
- Yes. There really is.
- Okay.

48:02.964 --> 48:05.133
That's all I need to know.
For now.

48:05.133 --> 48:07.218
You got to open.
I'll see you around.

48:07.302 --> 48:09.262
- Thank you.
- How many are you?

48:11.264 --> 48:12.974
Welcome to The Button Club,
folks!

48:12.974 --> 48:15.226
- Benny, who's your pal?
- Hey.

48:15.310 --> 48:17.979
<i>♪ If you want to have fun,
come home with me</i> ♪

48:17.979 --> 48:21.274
<i>♪ You can stay all night
and play with my TV</i> ♪

48:21.274 --> 48:24.444
<i>♪ TV is the thing this year,
this year</i> ♪

48:24.444 --> 48:27.030
<i>TV is the thing this year ♪</i>

48:27.030 --> 48:30.533
<i>♪ Radio was great,
now it's out of date...</i>

48:30.617 --> 48:33.244
How you feeling?
Feeling good? Feeling strong?

48:35.038 --> 48:37.040
Are you trying to speak?

48:37.040 --> 48:39.459
Tell me you did not
lose your fucking voice.

48:39.459 --> 48:41.294
I need to hear you
say something.

48:41.294 --> 48:43.212
I want to go home now.

48:43.296 --> 48:45.048
All right, then,
you're good to go.

48:45.048 --> 48:49.010
In five, four, three, two...

48:49.010 --> 48:50.762
Welcome back. Our next guest

48:50.762 --> 48:52.972
is no stranger to you.
Or to plates.

48:53.056 --> 48:54.432
It's the comedienne
Sophie Lennon,

48:54.432 --> 48:56.142
but don't turn that dial...

48:56.142 --> 48:58.269
- That's nice.
- ...because this is going to be

48:58.353 --> 48:59.979
a fascinating conversation.

49:00.063 --> 49:01.856
I'm gonna make sure.
Come on out here, Sophie.

49:01.856 --> 49:03.941
♪ ♪

49:18.665 --> 49:21.459
So... Sophie Lennon.

49:21.459 --> 49:24.462
Just how nutsy whacko are you?

49:29.425 --> 49:31.761
I believe the official diagnosis

49:31.761 --> 49:34.806
was "crazier
than an outhouse rat."

49:37.100 --> 49:38.601
- Good girl.
- Well,

49:38.685 --> 49:40.478
my producers told me you'd be
forthcoming this evening.

49:40.478 --> 49:42.563
- So far, so good.
- Great. So I can go now?

49:42.647 --> 49:44.816
- You sit right back down now, lady. You're not going anywhere.
- Oh.

49:44.816 --> 49:46.150
In fact, you and I
are gonna play a game.

49:46.234 --> 49:48.403
- Ooh, a game.
- Just a little True or False.

49:48.403 --> 49:50.446
I had my staff write down
some of the various rumors

49:50.530 --> 49:52.448
we've heard about you
over the years, and there are

49:52.532 --> 49:54.158
a lot of them. So,

49:54.242 --> 49:56.160
I'm gonna read them, and you
are gonna say if they are true

49:56.244 --> 49:58.204
- or false.
- Have at it.
- Here we go.

49:58.204 --> 49:59.580
Frank Sinatra
wrote a song about you.

49:59.664 --> 50:01.541
False. But it is true
that I'm a tramp.

50:01.541 --> 50:04.377
You once saved the life of a total stranger

50:04.377 --> 50:06.337
- choking in a restaurant.
- False.

50:06.421 --> 50:08.047
But I'm the one
who made up that rumor,

50:08.131 --> 50:09.757
and I'm glad to hear
it's still going around.

50:09.841 --> 50:12.635
You own a 300-acre ranch in Montana.

50:12.719 --> 50:14.971
Honestly, who doesn't?

50:14.971 --> 50:17.598
You punched Olivia de Havilland.

50:17.682 --> 50:19.142
She had it coming.

50:19.142 --> 50:21.561
- You punched Humphrey Bogart.
- Cried harder than Olivia.

50:21.561 --> 50:23.646
You're an addict.

50:23.730 --> 50:26.899
With multiple addictions.

50:26.983 --> 50:29.819
It's a long list.
You want to see it?

50:34.073 --> 50:36.701
- No, Gordon, this is dead wrong.
- It is.

50:36.701 --> 50:41.330
I can stop numbers three
and nine whenever I want.

50:43.249 --> 50:45.835
Ah. Well,

50:45.835 --> 50:47.670
- it's good to know there's no need to worry, then.
- Mm.

50:47.754 --> 50:50.006
You believe in intelligent life
on other planets.

50:50.006 --> 50:51.466
False. If there's none here,

50:51.466 --> 50:53.342
why would there be
intelligent life anywhere else?

50:53.426 --> 50:55.386
<i>-
- Very true. Next card.</i>

50:55.470 --> 50:58.514
<i>Um, you provide financially
for your 85-year-old mother.</i>

50:58.598 --> 51:00.016
<i>- Yes, that is true.
- And in exchange,</i>

51:00.016 --> 51:01.309
<i>you have her do the ironing.</i>

51:01.309 --> 51:02.727
Well,
when you stop working,

51:02.727 --> 51:04.520
<i>you start dying.</i>

51:04.604 --> 51:06.773
<i>That part is not true,
to be clear.</i>

51:06.773 --> 51:08.733
You forbid
your employees

51:08.733 --> 51:10.151
<i>from wearing certain perfumes...</i>

51:10.151 --> 51:12.612
- I'll get it.
- But you'll miss the show.

51:12.612 --> 51:15.281
There should be a way
to pause this.

51:15.281 --> 51:17.742
Like, you have a separate box

51:17.742 --> 51:20.203
recording the picture
and sound simultaneously.

51:20.203 --> 51:23.039
It should be able
to rewind, too.

51:23.039 --> 51:24.957
That's funny.

51:25.041 --> 51:27.084
<i>You once canceled a performance</i>

51:27.168 --> 51:28.377
<i>because you couldn't find
your Seconal.</i>

51:28.461 --> 51:29.962
Uh, no, I could find

51:30.046 --> 51:32.632
<i>my Seconal. I just couldn't find the stage.</i>

51:34.217 --> 51:36.719
Oh, that's lovely.

51:38.763 --> 51:42.350
It wasn't my fault.

51:42.350 --> 51:45.561
Oh! Uh, sorry.
My stage manager, Maury,

51:45.645 --> 51:47.104
is either practicing
for his dance recital,

51:47.188 --> 51:49.315
or he's motioning to me that
it's time for our next guest.

51:49.315 --> 51:51.359
But this being
<i>The Gordon Ford Show</i>

51:51.359 --> 51:53.569
and my being Gordon Ford,
I am making the decision

51:53.653 --> 51:55.822
to bump our next guest
because I want to keep talking

51:55.822 --> 51:57.281
to Sophie.
Is that okay with you, folks?

51:59.534 --> 52:01.536
- You got some more time for me, Sophie?
- Oh, I can even stay

52:01.536 --> 52:03.287
and clean up afterwards
if you want me to.

52:05.248 --> 52:08.376
So... what happened
that night, Sophie?

52:08.376 --> 52:10.753
The night
of your big Broadway debut?

52:12.505 --> 52:13.673
Hmm.

52:13.673 --> 52:15.883
- I got scared.
- Well,

